---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Section from '../../components/Section.astro';
import Button from '../../components/Button.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Revenue Performance Audit"
  description="Analytics integrity, conversion path analysis, and strategic synthesis. Finds where your data is lying and where revenue is leaking."
>
  <Section class="pt-28 pb-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-accent font-mono text-sm mb-4">The Get Right &rsaquo; Revenue Performance Audit</p>
      <h1 class="mb-6">Revenue Performance Audit</h1>
      <p class="text-accent text-lg font-medium mb-4">Powered by Delphi</p>
      <p class="text-secondary-text text-xl leading-relaxed">
        Measurement integrity, conversion path analysis, and the strategic synthesis
        that ties all three audits together. This is where the revenue numbers live
        &mdash; and where the unified 90-day execution plan is built.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section elevated>
    <h2 class="mb-8">Three layers of analysis</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-1 gap-6 max-w-3xl">
      <div class="bg-bg-surface border border-border-subtle rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="text-accent mb-3">Layer 1: Measurement Integrity</h4>
        <p class="text-secondary-text mb-4">Can you trust your data?</p>
        <ul class="text-secondary-text space-y-1.5 text-base">
          <li>Analytics tag firing, duplicates, and missing page coverage</li>
          <li>Goal and conversion setup validation</li>
          <li>Attribution model assessment</li>
          <li>Data hygiene (bot traffic, internal traffic, referral spam)</li>
          <li>Consent/privacy compliance impact on data collection</li>
          <li>Tool stack audit (installed, conflicting, redundant, missing)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-bg-surface border border-border-subtle rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="text-accent mb-3">Layer 2: Conversion Path Analysis</h4>
        <p class="text-secondary-text mb-4">Where is money leaking from your funnel?</p>
        <ul class="text-secondary-text space-y-1.5 text-base">
          <li>Funnel mapping with drop-off rates and revenue impact per stage</li>
          <li>Form friction analysis (fields, error handling, mobile vs desktop)</li>
          <li>CTA effectiveness (visibility, placement, intent matching)</li>
          <li>Page-level conversion matrix (traffic &times; conversion)</li>
          <li>Mobile conversion gap analysis</li>
          <li>Speed-to-conversion (ties Muttr findings to conversion loss in $)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-bg-surface border border-border-subtle rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="text-accent mb-3">Layer 3: Strategic Synthesis</h4>
        <p class="text-secondary-text mb-4">The keystone. All findings become one plan.</p>
        <ul class="text-secondary-text space-y-1.5 text-base">
          <li>Intake all findings from Muttr + Canary + Rev Ops layers 1-2</li>
          <li>Unified scoring: revenue impact &times; effort &times; dependency chain</li>
          <li>Produces the 90-day execution roadmap across all three pillars</li>
          <li>Revenue projection model (conservative / moderate / aggressive)</li>
          <li>Measurement plan with KPIs at 30 / 60 / 90 days</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section>
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <h2 class="mb-4">Where the experience shows</h2>
      <p class="text-secondary-text text-lg mb-6">
        The Revenue Performance Audit is the most founder-intensive piece of The Get Right.
        Tools can detect tag issues and map conversion paths. But synthesizing findings
        from three different audits into one coherent execution plan &mdash; prioritized
        by business impact, scoped to your team's capacity, and sequenced so fixes
        don't block each other &mdash; that takes 34 years of combined experience.
      </p>
      <p class="text-secondary-text text-lg">
        This pillar is why you always talk to the people who built the system.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section elevated>
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <h2 class="mb-4">How it connects</h2>
      <p class="text-secondary-text text-lg mb-6">
        The Revenue Performance Audit <span class="text-primary-text">owns the synthesis</span>.
        It takes technical findings from the Platform Audit and converts them to dollar
        amounts. It takes content gaps from the Content Audit and sequences them by
        conversion potential. Then it produces the single 90-day roadmap that your
        team actually executes against.
      </p>
      <p class="text-secondary-text text-lg">
        Without this pillar, you have two backlogs. With it, you have one plan.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section>
    <div class="text-center">
      <h2 class="mb-4">See the full engagement</h2>
      <p class="text-secondary-text text-lg mb-8 max-w-xl mx-auto">
        The Revenue Performance Audit only reaches its potential when paired with
        the other two pillars. That's why The Get Right runs all three together.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
        <Button href="/the-get-right">See The Full Get Right</Button>
        <Button href="/contact" variant="secondary">Talk to a Founder</Button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>
